content: Does not allow a "try before you buy". After purchase app loaded stations ONCE then nothing. Message sent to developer but NO response. Do not waste money on this app. There are others out there that function as described. This one does not..

content: The app continually stops working on my note 2.  I uninstall the app and reinstall it.  It works fine for several days and stops working  again.  I have uninstalled and reinstalled about 8 times now.  Getting frustrated.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback, we have confirmed the problem and are working on resolving it. UPDATE: It has been resolved.

content: I've been using the free Apple Aeroweather Lite version for 6 months now on an Ipod 5, and downloaded this for my new Samsung Galaxy S3 as soon as I got it this weekend.  I like the addition of the crosswind calculation, but I'm displeased that this pay version doesn't include the calculations for density altitude, pressure altitude, and freezing level like the free Apple version.  Having these on the Ipod saved me a lot of calculation time before a flight, so I'm definitely unhappy about them not being included on the Android version.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback, we are including these features in the upcoming update.

content: Simply says "unfortunately aeroweather has stopped working" every time I try to start it.
replyContent: Sorry to hear about the problem. We are looking into it. Meanwhile, try to remove and reinstall Aeroweather, and contact us with more details on your setup.

content: Quite disappointing with this app despite after reading most of the review. Taking more than 10seconds to load my group(consist of 8 aerodromes inside) and after adding the aerodromes, taking forever to update the metar and tafs.  Notam not working.  Hope to see improvement from developer.
replyContent: Could you tell us on which device this performance issue is?

content: I use this app everyday when I'm working but it needs better sorting. Please bring back the alphabetical sorting at least.
Needs to be able to name a list. (Or be easer to figure out how if I am missing something)
replyContent: Hi, Thanks for your review. You can change the name of a group when you press the right side of the cell that contains the group name.

content: The best aviation weather app
Not enough info on my local airports

Like the app in general although there is still room for some improvements. E.g. I'd like to see both metar and TAF in the of all airports. Quicker, better overview. Doesn't matter if I have to scroll down. An option maybe?
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback, we will see what we can do. We have added an option to call to the AWOS available stations. This was a requested feature that was available in the iOS version. For this, the app will require the appropriate permission.

content: Great app.  Much improved performance on my Nexus 7 with latest update.  I use it daily on both iOS and now Android.

I have been using AeoWeather for the flying I do on the Canadian East Coast for a few months now. I have it installed on both a GS3 and a Nexus 7. It has been running well on both devices, with accurate weather reports that update quickly and reliably. The one issue I have at the moment that prevents me from giving this app 5 stars is that I cannot download NOTAMS for airports not served by a weather observation, and that the NOTAMS excluded runway surface condition reports in Canada. I have contacted the developer and am hoping that they will find a solution to this problem. If they do, I will update this app to a 5 star rating.
No question, great.

Well worth paying the small price for. It works very well on my Samsung SIII, and gives far more information than most modern Airliners have available electronically in their flightdecks. A very useful feature is the "Group" function, allowing you to group airports by flight route, i.e. Airports on a North Pacific NOPAC route etc. After entering the airports, just sync it prior to flight then put your phone into flight mode. This app is excellent for tracking en-route airports with Met data and runway info.
It's a good and very useful app, my only gripe is that it doesn't include notams like the iPad / iPhone version does. If that's included in the next update, 5 stars.....
